fields.suggestion:
Load the secret from an environment variable:

```ts
const JWT_SECRET = process.env.JWT_SECRET;
if (!JWT_SECRET) throw new Error('JWT_SECRET is required');

const token = jwt.sign(payload, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '7d' });
```

fields.body:
The `findUser` call is not wrapped in a try/catch. If the database query fails, the error propagates as an unhandled rejection and crashes the process:

```ts
const user = await db.users.findUnique({ where: { id: req.params.id } });
res.json(user);
```

Also, if `user` is `null` this sends a `null` response with a 200 status.

fields.suggestion:
Add error handling and a proper 404:

```ts
try {
  const user = await db.users.findUnique({ where: { id: req.params.id } });
  if (!user) return res.status(404).json({ error: 'User not found' });
  res.json(user);
} catch (err) {
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
}
```

fields.body:
Each order fetches its items individually inside a loop:

```ts
const orders = await db.orders.findMany();
for (const order of orders) {
  order.items = await db.orderItems.findMany({ where: { orderId: order.id } });
}
```

For 100 orders this fires 101 queries.

fields.suggestion:
Use an `include` to eager-load the relation in a single query:

```ts
const orders = await db.orders.findMany({
  include: { items: true },
});
```

Restrict the origin to your actual frontend domains:

```ts
app.use(cors({
  origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS?.split(',') || ['https://app.acme.com'],
  credentials: true,
}));
```

fields.body:
The age check uses loose equality which causes unexpected coercion:

```ts
if (input.age == '0') {
  return 'Age cannot be zero';
}
```

This means `0 == '0'` evaluates to `true`, but `null == '0'` is `false` — missing the null case.

fields.suggestion:
Use strict equality and add a null check:

```ts
if (input.age === 0 || input.age == null) {
  return 'A valid age is required';
}
```
